   <mods:abstract>Recommends to Washington's attention Captain Eld of the British Guards.
            "His father is a gentleman of character, fortune, respectable connexions; and has been
            friendly to America from the beginning of the controversy." If partial exchanges are
            made, Sir James hopes that Eld will be among the first to be considered, and that in the
            meantime "every reasonable indulgence may be granted him." Encloses a pamphlet
            containing parliamentary speeches on the subject of American independence. Enclosure:
            [before 12 July 1782], pamphlet containing parliamentary speeches on the subject of
            American independence.</mods:abstract>
